# Deskly database connection (PostgreSQL).
#
# Variable names match what the Neon / Vercel Postgres integration injects,
# so production needs NO manual env vars — connecting the database is enough.
#
# ── Local development ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# Run `docker compose up -d` first, then copy this file to `.env`:
#   cp .env.example .env
# The defaults below match docker-compose.yml, so no edits are needed.
POSTGRES_PRISMA_URL="postgresql://deskly:deskly@localhost:5432/deskly?schema=public"
POSTGRES_URL_NON_POOLING="postgresql://deskly:deskly@localhost:5432/deskly?schema=public"

# ── Production (Neon / Vercel Postgres) ──────────────────────────
# Don't set these here. Connect a Neon/Vercel Postgres store to the project
# and it auto-injects POSTGRES_PRISMA_URL (pooled, used at runtime) and
# POSTGRES_URL_NON_POOLING (direct, used by Prisma migrations), among others.
